main event: A witness observed a crescent shaped object that changed in brightness from dim to bright in Seattle on multiple occasions in January 1956.
interesting points: The object was noted to be the size of a dime and was white and yellow in color., The observation lasted for approximately 1 hour and 30 minutes., The object was seen moving from east to west and faded away to the west., There were multiple reports of similar sightings on different dates., The data available was insufficient to conclusively identify the object.
